# LangChain Expression Language (LCEL) Mastery

This repository focuses on mastering the fundamentals of **LangChain Expression Language (LCEL)** using modern integration standards with Google's Gemini models. It transitions from traditional, legacy chains to modern, modular, production-ready AI pipelines.

---

## 🎯 Core Learning Objectives
* **Modular Pipelines:** Understanding the power of the `.pipe()` syntax to connect prompts, models, and parsing layers.
* **Streamlined Output Formatting:** Isolating conversational AI filler data to retrieve raw, actionable strings and structured JSON data.
* **Production-Ready Configuration:** Implementing secure environment variable patterns to prevent credentials from leaking into public repositories.

---

## 📁 Repository Structure

* **`LCEL_chain.js`** – A fundamental LCEL pipeline demonstrating the core `PromptTemplate -> Model -> StringOutputParser` workflow.
* **`LCEL_structured_Output.js`** – An advanced pipeline that binds strict schemas to the LLM, forcing the AI to respond in validated, predictable JSON structures.
* **`.env.example`** – A template file outlining necessary configuration keys for safe local setup.

---

## 🛠️ Built With

* **Runtime:** Node.js (v24+)
* **Framework:** LangChain Core (`@langchain/core`)
* **LLM Integration:** LangChain Google GenAI (`@langchain/google-genai`)
* **Data Validation:** Zod
* **Environment Management:** Dotenv

---

## 🚀 Local Installation & Setup

Follow these steps to set up and run this project locally:

### 1. Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone [https://github.com/SafiaMirbahar/LangChain-Expression-Language-LCEL-Mastery.git](https://github.com/SafiaMirbahar/LangChain-Expression-Language-LCEL-Mastery.git)
cd LANGCHAIN_DEV
